The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 July is 46,886 (5,426.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 July, there were 1,708 new confirmed cases (197.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 June, there were 876 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 95% (832 extra cases).
